{"id":5490,"date":"2022-12-14T00:53:00","date_gmt":"2022-12-14T00:53:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/?p=5490"},"modified":"2022-12-12T12:53:48","modified_gmt":"2022-12-12T12:53:48","slug":"seasons-greetings-from-kht","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/seasons-greetings-from-kht\/","title":{"rendered":"Season&#8217;s Greetings from KHT"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong><em>Everyone at KHT would like to wish you all a very happy holiday season and merry Christmas! As we move into 2023, we hope the new year is a happy and healthy one for us all. <\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This year has been one of change, development and new directions for KHT. With a new Director, new staff in the UK KHT team and new staff in Thailand, we are working to ensure we can efficiently support our projects, fundraising and improve the impact of our work for the Karen. You can read case studies and  KHT news on our <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/about-us\/news\/\">Latest News<\/a> page and meet our team and trustees <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/about-us\/meet-our-team\/\">here<\/a>. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To improve our WASH Programme we have introduced new filters, more water testing and improved monitoring and evaluation. Our Livelihoods Programme continues to make a vital impact on alleviating poverty and reducing food security for Karen villages and we continue to support Karen children and youth, including a new focus on health and education. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"5494\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/63502-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5494\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/63502-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/63502-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/63502-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/63502.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"480\" data-id=\"5493\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/64136-1024x480.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5493\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/64136-1024x480.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/64136-300x141.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/64136-768x360.jpg 768w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/64136.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We also welcomed volunteers back to Khun Yuam since the beginning of the Covid 19 Pandemic. You can read about their experiences <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/volunteer-diary-living-in-khun-yuam\/\">here<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/volunteer-diary-first-impressions-and-teaching-in-khun-yuam\/\">here<\/a>. We also held our annual Jungle Trek and welcome intrepid trekkers who are helping us raise vital funds whilst experiencing life in Karen villages and witnessing our work in action. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" data-id=\"5497\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/MicrosoftTeams-image-41-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5497\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/MicrosoftTeams-image-41-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/MicrosoftTeams-image-41-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/MicrosoftTeams-image-41-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/MicrosoftTeams-image-41.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"5496\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/\u0e42\u0e04\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e39_\u0e52\u0e52\u0e50\u0e53\u0e51\u0e57_60-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5496\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/\u0e42\u0e04\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e39_\u0e52\u0e52\u0e50\u0e53\u0e51\u0e57_60-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/\u0e42\u0e04\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e39_\u0e52\u0e52\u0e50\u0e53\u0e51\u0e57_60-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/\u0e42\u0e04\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e39_\u0e52\u0e52\u0e50\u0e53\u0e51\u0e57_60-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/\u0e42\u0e04\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e39_\u0e52\u0e52\u0e50\u0e53\u0e51\u0e57_60.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"960\" data-id=\"5495\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/302605529_1207833949996912_1701885219452624642_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5495\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/302605529_1207833949996912_1701885219452624642_n.jpg 720w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/302605529_1207833949996912_1701885219452624642_n-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We are thankful to all our donors, supporters, staff and volunteers for their support, donations and hard work. KHT&#8217;s success in 2022 has only been possible thanks to you. This year we:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Completed&nbsp;5&nbsp;WASH Systems and helped&nbsp;end water poverty for over 1700&nbsp;people.<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>Built&nbsp;our 100th Flood Resistant Irrigation System (FRIS) in Mae Hong Son.<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>Improved&nbsp;livelihoods for over 2899 people though 6 FRIS projects.<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>Ensured&nbsp;over 384 children are traveling&nbsp;safely to&nbsp;school and over 320 children are being fed nutritious meals at school.<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>Are helping&nbsp;46 Karen youth attend university or vocational studies.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We are moving into the new year with renewed intent on supporting the marginalised Karen people and we are grateful for your ongoing support! <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can support our campaigns by <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/get-involved\/donate\/\">donating<\/a>, join our <a href=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/drop-by-drop-help-us-end-water-poverty-for-the-karen-people\/\">Xmas awareness appeal <\/a>and follow us on social media and keep the momentum going into 2023 and beyond! <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"